{
  "stem": "23090.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the frightening thing about being a young person, a young child, at my age, which was six, six, seven years old-- no, it was six years old, is that, you know, traditionally, you come home, here, under normal conditions.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you kind of shield the bad things from children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You say let's not talk in front of a child about something bad that's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Let's be more positive and, and just expose them to the better, to the nice, niceties, niceties.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But unfortunately, everything in our existence in those days was so dismal and so morbid that there was just no good news.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was just nothing good that was, was, was happening.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were not yet aware of concentration camps and that sort of thing, but the impression to a young child was already nothing, but you-- you-- you-- you-- you envisioned, your imagination was death.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Death and death and death and death.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in one way, you were being prepared for what was happening, rather than just a, a, a sudden thing happening to you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, but it was a-- it was a scary and horrible, horrible way of growing up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And each day-- each day it got a little worse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And each day you started hearing the bombings, and then ultimately, these planes were just flying over on a round-the-clock basis, and just bombing and bombing and bombing and bombing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "While the Polish army was still fighting, which wasn't very long, but for the period of four or five weeks, we were subjected to a constant-- you know, the, the hissing of that bomb falling.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you get-- you never get used to that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you're scared to death of it.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
